{"id":41,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":41,"title":"Chapter 38: The Murder of the Chief Judge","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 38","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 38"],["h1","The Murder of the Chief Judge"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p3"},"Wicked men had become judges over the Nephites. They punished the righteous people but not the wicked people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/7.4-5"},"Helaman 7:4–5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p5"},"Nephi was sad to see so much wickedness among the people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/7.6-7"},"Helaman 7:6–7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p7"},"One day he was praying on a tower in his garden. His garden was by the highway that led to a marketplace in Zarahemla."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/7.10"},"Helaman 7:10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p9"},"People passing by on the highway heard Nephi praying. A large group gathered, wondering why he was so sad."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/7.11"},"Helaman 7:11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p11"},"When Nephi saw the people, he told them he was sad because of their wickedness. He told them to repent."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/7.12-14,17"},"Helaman 7:12–14, 17"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p13"},"He warned them that if they did not repent, their enemies would take their homes and cities and the Lord would not help them fight their enemies."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/7.22"},"Helaman 7:22"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p15"},"Nephi said the Nephites were more wicked than the Lamanites because the Nephites had been taught the commandments but were not obeying them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/7.24"},"Helaman 7:24"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p17"},"He said that if the Nephites did not repent, they would be destroyed."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/7.28"},"Helaman 7:28"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p19"},"Some of the wicked judges were there. They wanted the people to punish Nephi for speaking against them and their law."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/8.1-4"},"Helaman 8:1–4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p21"},"Some of the people agreed with the wicked judges. Others believed Nephi; they knew he was a prophet and spoke the truth."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/8.7-9"},"Helaman 8:7–9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p23"},"Nephi told the people that they had rebelled against God and would soon be punished if they did not repent."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/8.25-26"},"Helaman 8:25–26"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p25"},"Nephi told the people to go find their chief judge. He would be lying in his own blood, murdered by a brother who wanted his position."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/8.27"},"Helaman 8:27"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p27"},"Five men from the crowd ran to see the chief judge. They did not believe that Nephi was a prophet of God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.1-2"},"Helaman 9:1–2"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p29"},"When they saw Seezoram, the chief judge, lying in his blood, they fell to the ground in fear. Now they knew that Nephi was a prophet."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.3-5"},"Helaman 9:3–5"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p31"},"Seezoram’s servants had already found the chief judge and had run to tell the people. They returned and found the five men lying there."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.6-7"},"Helaman 9:6–7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p33"},"The people thought the five men had murdered Seezoram."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.8"},"Helaman 9:8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p35"},"They threw the five men into prison and then sent word throughout the city that the chief judge had been killed and that the murderers were in prison."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.9"},"Helaman 9:9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f18"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_18.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p37","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p37"},"The next day the people went to where the chief judge would be buried. The judges who had been at Nephi’s garden asked where the five men were."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p38","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p38"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.10-12"},"Helaman 9:10–12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f19"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_19.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p39","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p39"},"The judges asked to see the accused murderers."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p40","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p40"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.13"},"Helaman 9:13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f20"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_20.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p41","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p41"},"The accused murderers were the five men who had run from Nephi’s garden to the chief judge."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p42","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p42"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.13"},"Helaman 9:13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f21"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_21.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p43","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p43"},"The five men said they had found the chief judge lying in blood, just as Nephi had said. Then the judges accused Nephi of sending someone to murder Seezoram."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p44","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p44"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.15-16"},"Helaman 9:15–16"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f22"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_22.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p45","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p45"},"Knowing that Nephi was a prophet, the five men argued with the judges, but they would not listen. They had Nephi tied up."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p46","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p46"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.18-19"},"Helaman 9:18–19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f23"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_23.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p47","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p47"},"The judges offered Nephi money and his life if he would say he had plotted to kill the chief judge."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p48","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p48"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.20-21"},"Helaman 9:20–21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f24"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_24.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p49","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p49"},"Nephi told the judges to repent of their wickedness. Then he told them to go to Seantum, Seezoram’s brother."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p50","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p50"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.22,26"},"Helaman 9:22, 26"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f25"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_25.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p51","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p51"},"Nephi told them to ask Seantum if he and Nephi had plotted to murder Seezoram. Nephi said Seantum would say “no.”"]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p52","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p52"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.27-28"},"Helaman 9:27–28"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f26"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_26.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p53","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p53"},"Then the judges were to ask Seantum if he had killed his brother. Seantum would again say “no,” but the judges would find blood on his cloak."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p54","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p54"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.29-31"},"Helaman 9:29–31"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f27"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_27.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p55","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p55"},"Nephi said Seantum would then shake and turn pale and finally confess to killing his brother."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p56","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p56"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.33-35"},"Helaman 9:33–35"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f28"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_28.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p57","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p57"},"The judges went to Seantum’s house, and everything happened as Nephi said it would. Nephi and the five men were set free."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p58","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p58"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.37-38"},"Helaman 9:37–38"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.f29"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_041_29.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p59","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p59"},"As the people walked away from Nephi, some said he was a prophet; others said he was a god. Nephi went home, still sad about their wickedness."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p60","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-38-the-murder-of-the-chief-judge.p60"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/9.40-41"},"Helaman 9:40–41"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/10.2-3"},"Helaman 10:2–3"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
